Out doors is pretty nice, a lot of plants, dog friendly, and some tables. However, the smoking area is a bit of a turn off. I get it, its life, people smoke, but it's hard to want to bring my dog somewhere and sit down for a drink when I'm surrounded by ashes, cigg butts, and smoke. In response to the owner: Like I said, I get it. Smoking is part of bars. I probably should have been more specific. I believe the upkeep of the area should be improved. It wasn’t terribly busy when I visited. I have been to many bars around Brooklyn, and nearly every bar that has an outdoor area. I haven’t seen as much ash and as many butts on the ground in other places as I did here. The area is also more enclosed and tighter so it’s harder for the smoke to escape from what I witnessed. It’s just a bit disturbing to see my dog stand up and shake ashes out of her coat, especially when it’s requested they be on the floor. Thank you for your response.
